{
  "stem": "17761.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And again for the same problem, my father was born in the Bukovina, he wanted to go back to Bukovina.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so we ended up finally in a little town in the Bukovina, which is a beautiful place, marvelous sceneries there, called Vatra-Dornei, V-A-T-R-A dash D-O-R-N-E-I, called-- under the Austria-Hungarian rule, called Dorna-Watra, D-O-R-N-A-W-A-T-R-A.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there I've been until we were deported to the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that is where I spent my beautiful years of-- as a youngster, as a child and a youngster.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was born in another village in the neighborhood of Arbore called Balaceala, B-A-L-A-C-E-A-L-A, also county of Suceave, to a very-- to parents who were [NON-ENGLISH] Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father, by the way, was [NON-ENGLISH] Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were a little bit of competitive to each other.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a very interesting thing that a [NON-ENGLISH] married a [NON-ENGLISH] from the house of [NON-ENGLISH] Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a very honest, pious man, my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But to come back to my mother I'll perhaps say something about my grandparents also.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they married very young.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- it was an interesting thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The father of the bride, of my mother, sent a commission, a committee to the house of my father's parents to see if he is a [NON-ENGLISH], if he knows something, who this guy was-- is.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they found him probably adequate, because the result was they ended and they-- and they married.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she-- most of her years, she was a housewife, until later on when we came to Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that's already a story for later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's full name is Iuta Feigi, I-U-T-A another name F-E-I-G-I.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Family name was Hass, H-A- double S.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
